{
  "answer": "**In Chapter 1 of the *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, the dharma of the householder (*gṛhasthadharmaprakaraṇam*) is described explicitly in section 5.**[^1]\n\nThis section begins with the subsection title at paragraph [p-a80877] and opens with verse 1.97 (*Yj_1.97*), which prescribes the householder's daily performance of Smārta and Śrauta rites in the appropriate fires.[^2] It continues through verses 1.97–1.128 (up to paragraph [p-e13112]), covering daily rituals (e.g., twilight worship, the five great sacrifices, hospitality to guests), feeding dependents, general conduct (non-violence, truth, etc.), varṇa-specific duties, and rules on living modestly without excessive accumulation.[^3] The section then transitions to \"6. The Duties of the Graduate\" (*snātakadharmaprakaraṇam*) at paragraph [p-763993].[^4]\n\n[^1]: *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, Chapter 1, section 5 heading, [/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-a80877](https://thothica.org/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-a80877).\n\n[^2]: *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, Chapter 1, [/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-6c5d0a](https://thothica.org/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-6c5d0a).\n\n[^3]: *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, Chapter 1, section 5 (verses 1.97–1.128), [/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-a80877](https://thothica.org/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-a80877).\n\n[^4]: *Yājñavalkya Smṛti*, Chapter 1, section 6 heading, [/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-763993](https://thothica.org/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-763993).",
